                            <comment id="231936" author="jamesanunez" created="Tue, 14 Aug 2018 18:50:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Whenever we see recovery-small test 26a to fail with the &apos;&apos;timeouts are wrong! mds: 100, client: 20, TIMEOUT=20&apos;&apos; error message, we also see that a previous test, recovery-small test 23, fails with a ping/pm issue (DCO-8171)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 4 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 3 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 2 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 1 secs left ...
waiting for trevis-8vm11 to fail attempts=3
+ pm -h powerman --off trevis-8vm11
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 4 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 3 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 2 secs left ...
waiting ! ping -w 3 -c 1 trevis-8vm11, 1 secs left ...
waiting for trevis-8vm11 to fail attempts=3
trevis-8vm11 still pingable after power down! attempts=3
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The converse is not true; recovery-small test 23 fails some times and test 26a does not fail.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="231930" author="adilger" created="Tue, 14 Aug 2018 17:58:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like it is test script fallout from test_23 failing to restart the MDS for some reason.  It doesn&apos;t appear to be an actual Lustre bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
